### Key Technical Choices

1.  **CSS Transitions over JS Animation Loops**: I used `transition: transform` with a `cubic-bezier` timing function. This gives that classic "heavy reel" feel where it starts fast and slows down smoothly, without needing a heavy animation library. Citations:[] PromptCitations:[] TraceID:ea2d9fd6642838e0 ServerTiming:gfet4t7; dur=13184 NetPlusServerTiming:13.332343s TimeToFirstToken:13.332343s DetectedIntent: ProcessingDetails:{RagStatus:RAG_DISABLED AtlasExperience:21d71049fd93e459 PromptID: CompletionMethod: ExperimentDebugStringFingerprint: ModelURI: ChatClientIDHash: MetricMetadata:map[] ModelConfig:{ID:chat-gemini-3-0-flash-preview-free-tier DisplayName:3 Flash Preview DescriptionText:}} AgentProcessingDetails:0xaeffdd0a510 YieldInfo:<nil> MoAInfo: MoAWorkerInfo:[] WorkspaceChange:<nil> FileUsage:0xaeffe8b2370 Disclaimer: SuggestedPrompts:[] AgentToolCalls:[] AgentMessages:[] ThinkingSummaryMarkdown: AgentMetadata:{CoderAgent:{Kind:} Model: Error: UserTier: TraceID:}}
